==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Trundle-bed
<hw>Trun"dle-bed`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A low bed that
is moved on trundles, or little wheels, so that it can be pushed under a
higher bed; a truckle-bed; also, sometimes, a simiral bed without
wheels.</def> <rj><au>Chapman.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Trundlehead</ent>⟦br⟧
